<p>Neither the National Cancer Institute (NCI) nor does the Early Detection Research Network (EDRN) endorse or recommend any commercial products, processes, or services. Therefore, mention of commercial products, processes, or services on EDRN's web site, edrn.nic.nih.gov, cannot be construed as an endorsement or recommendation.</p>
<p>The EDRN web site provides links to other internet sites for informational purposes and the convenience of its users. When users select a link to an external web site, they are leaving the EDRN web site and are subject to the privacy and security policies of the owners/sponsors of the external site.</p>
<p>Neither NCI nor EDRN endorse organizations that sponsor linked, external web sites. In addition, neither NCI nor EDRN endorse products or services that such organizations may offer. Furthermore, neither NCI nor EDRN control or guarantee the currency, accuracy, relevance, or completeness of information found on linked, external web sites.</p>
<p>Neither NCI nor EDRN can authorize the use of copyrighted materials published on linked, external web sites. Users must request authorization from the sponsors of those web sites.</p>
<p>Neither NCI nor EDRN is not responsible for transmissions users may receive from linked, external web sites.</p>
<p>Neither NCI nor EDRN guarantee that linked, external web sites comply with Section 508 (Accessibility Requirements) of the Rehabilitation Act.</p>
<p>Press releases or other materials meant for public use will not be posted on the EDRN web site unless developed by or for NCI, for EDRN, or for the National Institutes of Health.</p>
<p>In general, it is neither NCI's nor EDRN's intention to provide specific medical advice to users of its web site, but rather to provide users with information to help them better understand their health, diagnosed conditions, and the current range of approaches related to cancer treatment, prevention, screening, and supportive care. Both NCI and EDRN urge users to consult with a qualified physician for diagnosis and for answers to their personal medical questions.</p>
